{"id":103,"date":"2022-12-11T09:02:10","date_gmt":"2022-12-11T14:02:10","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/alfredoromero.com\/?p=103"},"modified":"2022-12-11T09:02:11","modified_gmt":"2022-12-11T14:02:11","slug":"crypotocurrencies-challenges-and-opportunities-for-monetary-policy","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"http:\/\/alfredoromero.com\/crypotocurrencies-challenges-and-opportunities-for-monetary-policy\/","title":{"rendered":"Crypotocurrencies: Challenges and Opportunities for Monetary Policy"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p id=\"block-10995b85-0415-483f-9dcb-59eeb7d36919\"><strong>Presented in 2020 during the Blockchain Symposium, organized by North Carolina A&amp;T State University<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p id=\"block-ac5e1e5c-ce92-4471-ad38-fb7e380c2dc9\">&#8220;A cryptodollar would still work as a semi-anonymous medium of exchange accessible to banks and the population under a system that may be cheaper and easier to manage than a cash system. During debates for the CARES Act, an idea for a government issued digital wallet was floated under which Congress would authorize the Federal Reserve to create <em>FedAccounts<\/em>. They would allow U.S. residents, citizens and businesses located in the country to access financial services,&#8221; said Dr. Alfredo Romero during his talk: &#8220;<a href=\"http:\/\/alfredoromero.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/Romero-Blockchain-Symposium.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Crypotocurrencies: Challenges and Opportunities for Monetary Policy<\/a>.&#8221; <\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"777\" height=\"283\" src=\"http:\/\/alfredoromero.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/Picture1.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-106\" srcset=\"http:\/\/alfredoromero.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/Picture1.png 777w, http:\/\/alfredoromero.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/Picture1-300x109.png 300w, http:\/\/alfredoromero.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/Picture1-768x280.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 777px) 100vw, 777px\" \/><\/figure>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Presented in 2020 during the Blockchain Symposium, organized by North Carolina A&amp;T State University &#8220;A cryptodollar would still work as a semi-anonymous medium of exchange<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":106,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[14],"tags":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"http:\/\/alfredoromero.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/103"}],"collection":[{"href":"http:\/\/alfredoromero.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"http:\/\/alfredoromero.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/alfredoromero.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/alfredoromero.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=103"}],"version-history":[{"count":3,"href":"http:\/\/alfredoromero.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/103\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":107,"href":"http:\/\/alfredoromero.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/103\/revisions\/107"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/alfredoromero.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/106"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"http:\/\/alfredoromero.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=103"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/alfredoromero.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=103"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/alfredoromero.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=103"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}